    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prehistoric biface stone tools, usually u-shaped, large and oblong, with transverse cutting edges. Thought to be used for heavy digging, the slaughter of animals, skinning game, and bone breaking.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
